'''Whitton Baptist Church''' is a church in Hounslow Road, [[Whitton, London|Whitton]] in [[Richmond upon Thames]], [[London]]. It is a member of the [[Baptist Union of Great Britain#Structure|London Baptist Association]].<ref name="London Baptist">{{cite web | url=http://www.londonbaptist.org.uk/resources/weblinks/london/ | title=London | publisher=[[London Baptist Association]] | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

==History==
The two foundation stones set into the front wall of the church carry the date October 20, 1934.<ref name="History"/> The present church building was opened on 6 April 1935. The new building, financed by the sale of [[St Margarets, London|St Margarets]] Baptist Church, replaced Whitton Gospel Hall which had opened in 1881.<ref name="History">{{cite web | url=http://www.whittonbaptist.co.uk/ | title=Our history | publisher=Whitton Baptist Church | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

The church's halls were opened in September 1968 on the site of an old tennis court. They replaced two previous halls, one of which was destroyed in a fire in 1966, and the other on a site which is now part of the church's car park.<ref name="History"/>

==Ministers==
:1936 Rev. Walter G. Davis
:1943 Rev. Albert Cassidy
:1970 Rev. Derek Buckingham 
:1976 Rev. Barry Vendy
:1984 Rev. Martin Smith
:1998 Rev. Andy Gore
:2014 Rev. Gordon Hindmarch<ref name="History"/>

